# Session Tracking Rule

On `save` shortcut or major task completion, save session state to `.local/sessions/raw/[YYYY-MM-DD].md`:

   ```markdown
   ## 14:30

   - Did: [what was done]
   - Files: [files changed]
   - Decided: [key decisions made]
   ```

   First entry of the day includes `# Session — YYYY-MM-DD` header. Subsequent entries just append `## HH:MM` blocks.

   Example: `.local/sessions/raw/2026-05-29.md`

   Path resolves to the main repo's `.local/sessions/` folder — shared across all worktrees, gitignored.

2. **Extract key corrections** and append them to `.local/sessions/corrections.md` so the AI can read them on next startup.

The `.local/` folder is gitignored and lives in the main repo, so it persists across worktrees.
